        <!-- Function Texts -->
        <text name="function_roofSolarPanelsOption" text="This building has an option to add solar panels on its roof. Price per panel: 265 $. Income per panel per month: 21.6 $ (with adequate weather conditions)." />
        <text name="function_heiferStable" text="This shelter is intended for heifers. Here they can grow up and should then be moved to another cow barn. Cows in this shelter do not produce milk or liquid manure, but they still produce manure." />
        <text name="function_cowYoungShelter" text="This shelter is intended for calves or heifers. Here they can grow up and should then be moved to another cow barn. Animals in this shelter do not produce milk or liquid manure, but they still produce manure." />
        <text name="function_calfHut" text="This hut is intended for calves only. Here they can grow up and must be moved to another cow barn. Animals in this enclosure do not produce milk or liquid manure, only manure, and they require a lot of manual daily care!" />
        <text name="function_bunkerSiloCC" text="This bunker silo can be filled with chaff, grass, alfalfa, and clover. After compacting and covering the silo, the contents convert into silage. NOTE: If the Maize Plus mod is used, the functionality of this silo changes to M+ standards." />
        <text name="function_grainStorage" text="This multipurpose facility features a large storage hall allowing crops to be stored on the ground or kept before processing, with plenty of space even for vehicles. The shredder produces food for your animals. Grain can also be stored in large-capacity silos." />
        <text name="function_fillableLiquidFertilizerAndHerbicideTanks" text="These tanks can be filled with liquid fertilizer and herbicide." />
        <text name="function_baleStorageCC" text="This building can be used to store your bales." />
        <text name="function_palletStorage" text="This building can be used to store your pallets." />
        <text name="function_orchard" text="Orchards produce fruit. They require water, liquid fertilizer, and compost." />
        <text name="function_greenhouseAdvanced" text="Advanced greenhouses produce vegetables faster but require more care. Needs: water, liquid fertilizer, and compost." />
        <text name="function_compostSilo" text="A compost silo can be filled with organic waste. After compacting and covering the silo, the contents convert into compost." />
        <text name="function_compost" text="Compost is required for orchards and greenhouses. It can also be used as fertilizer on fields." />
        <text name="function_heapSpawnerStoneCC" text="Stones can be collected free of charge from this building. Produces 3,000 units of stone per hour." />
        <text name="function_heapSpawnerLimestone" text="Limestone can be collected free of charge from this building. Produces 2,800 units of limestone per hour." />
        <text name="function_heapSpawnerClay" text="Clay can be collected free of charge from this building. Produces 1,600 units of clay per hour." />
        <text name="function_heapSpawnerIronOre" text="Iron ore can be collected free of charge from this building. Produces 800 units of iron ore per hour." />
        <text name="function_rentalHouse" text="This house is intended for rent and generates a profit of:" />
        <text name="function_rentalHouse01Income" text="2,500 $ per month" />
        <text name="function_rentalHouse02Income" text="3,000 $ per month" />
        <text name="function_rentalHouse03Income" text="2,000 $ per month" />
        <text name="function_chainlinkFenceBigGatePlacement" text="PLACEMENT NOTE: Make sure to place the gate parallel to the fence and on flat terrain for correct aesthetics." />
        <text name="function_decorativeGrass" text="This grass does not grow. It remains in its current stage and serves as decorative grass." />
        <text name="function_decorativeGardenCrops" text="This is a decorative garden crop and is not functional. It changes visuals depending on the season or disappears during specific times such as winter. (Depending on when it was painted, seasonal changes may start the following year. This also depends on whether seasonal growth is enabled. If seasonal growth is disabled, the appearance changes every in-game day.)" />
